response.overview: Vibrant, salt-of-the-earth comic Sarah Callaghan brings to the stage a powerhouse mash-up of comedy and self penned spoken word poetry about gangs, fitting in and feeling left out. From Piers Morgan and Micheal McIntyre to identity politics and the #MeToo Movement, no stone is left unturned in Sarahâ€™s quest to find out what it means to belong in this upfront, personal and punchy hour.
